Let $(R,\mm,K)$ be a regular local ring containing a field $k$ such that
either char $k=0$ or char $k=p$ and tr-deg $K/\BF_p\geq 1$. Let
$g_1,\ldots,g_t$ be regular parameters of $R$ which are linearly independent
modulo $\mm^2$. Let $A=R_{g_1\cdots g_t} [Y_1,\ldots,Y_m,f_1(l_1)^{-1},\ldots,
f_n(l_n)^{-1}]$, where $f_i(T)\in k[T]$ and $l_i=a_{i1}Y_1+\ldots+a_{im}Y_m$
with $(a_{i1},\ldots,a_{im})\in k^m-(0)$. Then every projective $A$-module of
rank $\geq t$ is free. Laurent polynomial case $f_i(l_i)=Y_i$ of this result is
due to Popescu.